Class MemAbstraction

  • java.lang.Object
    • dreisoft.tresos.generator.ng.api.cds.CDSGenScope.Attribute

  • public class MemAbstraction
extends CDSGenScope.Attribute
    Every Autosar module must support the mapping of resources. To map resources independent of the used compiler, the usage of macros is required.

    • Method Detail

      • createDefault

        public static MemAbstraction createDefault(java.lang.String module,
                                           java.lang.String memTypePostfix)
        Creates a new MemAbstraction scope attribute generating the default name structure for startIdentifier and endIdentifier. This method is the same as new MemAbstraction( module +"_START_"+ memTypePostfix, module +"_STOP_"+ memTypePostfix ); .
        Parameters:
        module - The name of the autosar module (e.g. EEP), never null.
        memTypePostfix - The postfix of the memory type identifier (e.g. SEC_VAR_16BIT), never null.
        Returns:
        A new MemAbstraction with default looking memory type identifiers.
        Since:
        2008.b
